Cross-examined. Q. You do not mean to say, that on the day he paid you 3l. 4s. 6d. he had attended Miss Doyle? A. Yes, he had; he had on the same day taken some goods to Mr. Maitland, in Bryanstone-square, about two or three o'clock - he rendered this account to me about seven or eight in the evening; the persons in the shop give in what they receive as soon as the customer is gone - but they give an account in the evening of what they have received in the course of the day - I saw the prisoner write this account in pencil;
Joseph Haines
is a cousin of mine- here are five items on one of these bills, and only three on the other.
